article.headline: Texas Southern 76, Grambling St. 68
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Jacques Jones scored 22 points and Dominique White scored 20 to help Texas Southern defeat Grambling 76-68 last night. Chris Moore scored 11 and Sollie Norwood 10 for Texas Southern (12-11, 8-4 SWAC), which led 37-29 at halftime. Texas Southern never trailed and led by as much as 15 in the second half. Andre' Ratliff and Anthony Williams each scored 23 for Grambling (10-10, 8-5 SWAC), while Jamal Breaux had 13 rebounds.
